text.tspan: - clean up the click handling in ViewController
v style should just be levels and colors
- plus dashes and arrows for links
v Create Objs that can be parented
v Structure of clones will be built and destroyed by the parent Component
- Can have multi level of clonings
v Fundamental edits will be applied to the lowest Obj
- Others will be applied to the element
- Link is part of the source El
v objs are flat, filled with objs and clones
- on clone base edit, edit the obj
- copy all clones (and their path) of the same obj
- save to a temp ref obj
- find the difference of path from original parent to the new one
- apply the same change to the ids in the temp ref obj
- when new clones are created, check the temp ref for matching id, and copy state if exists
- link between objs/clones is cloned to link between clones with the same id transform (if found)
- cloned links are the same link object
- if an obj/clone finds a matching pair, it adds itself and the pair to the link
- when removed, also remove self and the pair from link
- link checks if both objs in a pair are not hidden before rendering that clone
- if a link has no trg, it deletes itself
- rect selection by checking rect of all clones
- when an clone is put into another, only allow when the level is lower
- when changing level, only allow to be lower than parent and higher than children
- for each mutation, if recording, add copy of the state
- on undo/redo just completely replace the state
- for the text, use hidden component for each master to facilitate searching, resulting in highlights
- when obj is not selected, use a div that can be split to multiple, highlighted spans
- when searching, use the master components and the obj text spans
- add multi search for multi highlights with different colors
- split search term to highlight partial matches
- when replacing, replace the text in the master directly
- when selecting 1 obj, also search and highlight (in the background)
- when an clone component can't find its ref
- for key get val, refVal, and endVal
- if type doesn't have key, get from refObj as val
- if type is obj, use state as val
- either set var and refVal from state and refState, and endVal from overlay of both
- if endVal is deeply different, break, set as undefined
- if key is children or clones, make uneditable
- else, if clone, set on obj ref
- so links can be easily deeply compared, el to link is object, while link to els is id
- on edit, existing links will be deeply edited
